OL,3,CRenewables overtake coal globally for
OL,4,Cfirst time on record ` analysis
OL,6,FThe findings indicate that global
OL,7,Felectricity demand rose 2.6% in the
OL,8,Ffirst half of 2025 ` up 369 terawatt
OL,9,Fhours (TWh) compared to the first half
OL,10,Fof last year.
OL,12,FBut in terms of supply, renewables
OL,13,Fgenerated 5,072 TWh of global
OL,14,Felectricity ` which marked an increase
OL,15,Fof 4,709 TWh from the first six month
OL,16,Fof 2024, Ember said.
OL,18,FThis means renewables were found to
OL,19,Fhave overtaken coal generation at
OL,20,F4,896 TWh, which was down by 0.3% or
OL,21,F31 TWh year-on-year.
