OL,3,CRenewables overtake coal globally for
OL,4,Cfirst time on record ` analysis
OL,6,FThe analysis also suggests that solar
OL,7,Fand wind together grew quickly enough
OL,8,Fthat they can now meet total demand
OL,9,Fgrowth in some circumstances, while
OL,10,Ffossil fuels saw a global decline.
OL,12,FSolar met 83% of the rise because of a
OL,13,Frecord growth in generation in
OL,14,Fabsolute terms, equating to 306
OL,15,Fterawatt hours and a 31% year-on-year
OL,16,Frise, Ember said.
OL,18,FMeanwhile, the total decline in fossil
OL,19,Ffuel generation was found to be 0.3% `
OL,20,Fa reduction of 27 TWh.
